605. accersere is so frequently found in the best MSS. (for Plautus see the examples collected by Gruter on Cae. 111 4, 10 3 for Caesar Din- ter’s note on b. 9. 1 31, 4) that it would be very arbitrary simply to condemn this form, because we cannot explain it grammatically. There certainly can be no doubt that arcessere is the genuine form: ar being another form of the preposition ad (Corssen, auespr. 1, 89) and cesso the intensive of cio.
